<p>NOTES: Prior year comparisons are affected by several unusual items in the first quarter of 1997. Cadence and Integrated Measurement Systems Inc (IMS) completed a secondary offering of IMS stock, which reduced Cadence's ownership in IMS from 55 percent to 37 percent. Consequently, IMS' results are not consolidated in the Cadence's first quarter 1997 results. As 1996 financial statements consolidate IMS, year-on-year comparisons are affected.</p>
<p>In addition, Cadence recorded a one-time gain of $11.8 million primarily related to the IMS secondary offering. The first quarter results also include unusual charges of $11.7 million related to severance and other expenses associated with restructuring pursuant to Cadence's merger with High Level Design Systems and the write-off of in-process research and development expenses related to its merger with Synthesia AB.</p>
